{"title":"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote Gives SRAM 1X Cockpits Extra Functionality","link":"https://bikerumor.com/oneup-drop-bar-paddle-remote/","date":1730231445000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--1536x1024.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote on the bike\" /></p>\n<p>Have you ever looked at your SRAM 11spd 1X shifter and thought, <em>“I wish someone would do something with this space.”</em> Do you have an awkwardly placed drop bar dropper lever and despise the ergonomics? Well, OneUp has a solution for you. Introducing the OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--scaled.webp\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(All Images: OneUp)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote</strong> – What is it? </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, 1X SRAM riders can use the open space in the left shifter with OneUp’s super-sleek dropper remote setup. The new OneUp Components Drop Bar Remote provides an elegant solution for running a dropper post using 11-speed SRAM 1X (cable) levers. The design is seamless in aesthetics, and it looks like a factory lever, with only the OneUp logo laser etched on the side giving away the secret. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--scaled.webp\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote live\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-live--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>OneUp says, <em>“The design combines top-tier ergonomics, a lightweight lever feel, and seamless integration, setting a new standard for mechanical drop-bar remotes.”</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--scaled.webp\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote close up\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-close-up--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>SRAM 11spd Only </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Unfortunately, if you’re a Shimano rider or have the new SRAM APEX 12-spd, you can’t use this upgrade—yet (we’re hoping). The design is only for SRAM 11spd hydraulic groupsets with cable-actuated shifters. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--scaled.webp\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote product page\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-product-page--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The SRAM 11spd-only compatibility puts the OneUp drop bar paddle remote in a niche category. But there are so many of those levers floating around that I imagine they won’t have any problems filling the orders. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--1536x1024.webp\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote pre install\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-pre-install--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--1536x1024.webp\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote install video\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--2048x1365.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-install-video--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>What about mechanical APEX 12 spd? </em></strong>We have a review bike with the new SRAM APEX 12-speed, and the internal fitting for the shifting mechanism is slightly different. Hopefully, we will see an option for other mechanical shifting bodies in the future. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2.jpg\" alt=\"closeup of a oneup v3 dropper seatpost on a bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/OneUp-Components-V3-Dropper-Post-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Dropper Compatibility </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The remote is engineered for perfect compatibility with the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/oneup-components-v3-dropper-post-gets-lighter-smoother/\">OneUp V3 Dropper Post</a>. For those looking to use other posts (as there are many out there), we’re guessing you should be OK. However, Oneup has this disclaimer on the <a href=\"https://www.oneupcomponents.com/products/drop-bar-paddle-remote\">Drop Bar Paddle Remote landing page</a>. <em>“This product should also work with most brands’ dropper posts, but we cannot guarantee fitment and performance – except the OneUp V3/V2 Dropper Post. If you buy this paddle to actuate another brand’s dropper, you do so at your own risk.”</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Can I Install It Myself? </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>From what we’ve seen in the installation video, the OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote isn’t too hard to install, and you don’t need much to facilitate a successful installation. If you’re curious, check out the OneUp video below. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>How about service? </strong></em>The design facilitates easy removal of the dropper post for service. The cable clamp is positioned in the remote, and the cable end is within the dropper post, similar to other OneUp lever designs. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>OneUp added an integrated cable tensioner. This integrated design eliminates the need for an in-line barrel adjuster and supports entirely internal cable routing.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--scaled.webp\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote on the road\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-road--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote </strong>Product Specifications</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Material:</strong> 6061-T6 Aluminum Black Ano </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Size: </strong>80mm x 34mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight: </strong>32 g (lever assembly only, not including cable or housing)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--scaled.webp\" alt=\"OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote on the bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--2048x1366.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/OneUp-Drop-Bar-Paddle-Remote-on-the-bike--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote </strong>Compatibility</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>SRAM Red 11spd Hydro R</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM Force 11spd Hydro R</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM Rival 11spd Hydro R</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM Apex 11spd Hydro R</li>\n\n\n\n<li><em><strong>Not compatible with ETap, Apex 12spd, or Shimano</strong></em></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Pricing – <strong>OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>USD – $69.99, CAD – $95.99, GBP – £57.99, EUR – €63.99 and ROW – $81.99</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Available now at<a href=\"https://www.oneupcomponents.com\" target=\"_blank\"> oneupcomponents.com</a> with free worldwide shipping or from your local bike shop.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/oneup-drop-bar-paddle-remote/\">OneUp Drop Bar Paddle Remote Gives SRAM 1X Cockpits Extra Functionality</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"9ec96bdacf91eff3614cf2c91b342c4c7d601c592bd31a17fe29fe5883495290","category":"Cycling"}